(12, 1, '2021-08-31 10:15:54', '2021-08-31 09:15:54', '<b>Fender Player Series Jazz Bass - Maple Neck and Fingerboard, Buttercream Finish, and Two Player Series Single Coil Pickups</b>\r\n\r\nThe Fender Player Series is brand Available To Order Now, and is continuing the tradition of the Fender Standard series, in bringing you an awesome array of guitars and basses at a great price.\r\n\r\nWhether it\'s a Tele, a Strat, or even a P-Bass you want, the Fender Player Series has got you covered!\r\n<h3>Affordable And Versatile - What More Could You Want?</h3>\r\nOriginally introduced to the world in 1960 under the moniker Deluxe Model, the Fender Jazz bass was soon renamed and, due to its thinner and more-rounded neck than the P-Bass, marketed towards Jazz musicians. This dual single-coil design has stood the test of time, and is still one of the world\'s most popular bass guitars, almost six decades after its introduction.\r\n\r\nWith this Player Series Jazz Bass you get an inspiring instrument, that features the classic, elevated style and authentic Fender bass tone as its predecessors, but like the Standard Series before it, this bass can be yours for an incredible price.\r\n\r\n<strong>Versatility is the Key</strong>\r\n\r\nRenowned for their growling single-coil pickups, that offer plenty of articulation and thump, this modern take on the Fender Jazz bass offers you tones that are suitable for a wide array of musical styles, from pop, funk, jazz, rock and roll, to even more modern styles of rock and metal music - the world is your oyster!\r\n\r\n<strong>Classic Jazz Bass Stylings</strong>\r\n\r\nFeaturing a \"Modern C\" profiled maple neck, with matching maple fingerboard, and a 9.5\" fingerboard radius, the Fender Player Series Jazz Bass is suited to almost any playing style or skill level. Want to throw out some tasty Jaco-esque chops? No problem. Want to pop and slap like Flea? It can do that too. Want to use a pick and thump out some rock-solid AC/DC style bass lines? It\'s got you covered.\r\n\r\nIn fact, you\'d struggle to find a particular playing style that this bass isn\'t suitable for!\r\n\r\n<strong>Rock Solid Construction</strong>\r\n\r\nFrom the solid alder body, to the smooth maple neck, dual single coil pickups, and even the 4-saddle bridge, every inch of this incredible bass has been specially designed to offer you an incredible playing experience, that\'s available to you at a great price.\r\n\r\n<strong>Order Yours Today</strong>\r\n\r\nIf you\'d like to query the availability of this excellent bass, be sure to contact our Online Sales Team directly - they\'re always more than happy to help. Don\'t forget: if you place your order Online, you can choose from our excellent range of Home Delivery options!\r\n\r\nOrder this bass online and make use of our fantastic range of home delivery options!\r\n\r\n<strong>Technical Specs</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong>Model Series:</strong> Fender Player Series</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Instrument Type:</strong> Jazz Bass</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Body Material:</strong> Alder</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Body Finish:</strong> Gloss Polyester</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Colour:</strong> Buttercream</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Pickguard Material:</strong> 3-Ply Parchment</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Neck Material:</strong> Maple</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Neck Finish:</strong> Satin Urethane Finish on Back, Gloss Urethane Finish on Front</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Neck Profile:</strong> \"C\" Shape</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Fingerboard Material:</strong> Maple</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Fingerboard Radius:</strong> 9.5\"</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Fingerboard Inlays:</strong> Black Dots</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Frets:</strong> 20, Medium Jumbo</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Scale Length:</strong> 34\"</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Nut Material:</strong> Synthetic Bone</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Nut Width:</strong> 1.5\"</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Pickup Configuration:</strong> 2 x Single Coil</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Neck Pickup:</strong> Player Series Single Coil Jazz Bass Neck</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Bridge Pickup:</strong> Player Series Single Coil Jazz Bass Bridge</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Controls:</strong> Volume 1 (Neck), Volume 2 (Bridge), Master Tone</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Control Knobs:</strong> Vintage Style Black Plastic Jazz Bass</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Tuners:</strong> Standard Open-Gear</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Hardware Finish:</strong>Nickle/Chrome</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Fender Player Jazz Bass MN', '<b>Fender Player Series Jazz Bass - Maple Neck and Fingerboard, Buttercream Finish, and Two Player Series Single Coil Pickups</b>\r\n\r\nThe Fender Player Series is brand Available To Order Now, and is continuing the tradition of the Fender Standard series, in bringing you an awesome array of guitars and basses at a great price.\r\n\r\nWhether it\'s a Tele, a Strat, or even a P-Bass you want, the Fender Player Series has got you covered!', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'fender-player-jazz-bass-mn', '', '', '2021-09-01 14:00:25', '2021-09-01 13:00:25', '', 0, 'http://localhost/?post_type=product&#038;p=12', 0, 'product', '', 0),
