(76, 1, '2021-08-31 14:45:19', '2021-08-31 13:45:19', '<strong>Mustang Bass PJ</strong> – another great addition to Fender’s Offset series. Seen here in an retro Aged Natural, this versatile bass gives you the best of both worlds thanks its PJ pickup configuration.\r\n\r\nPrecision Bass or Jazz Bass – Get You a Bass That Can Do Both\r\n\r\nOriginally introduced back in 1964, the Mustang bass has been hugely popular for over fifty years, due in no small part to its versatility and has been used by bassists in a variety of bands including such diverse acts as The Rolling Stones and My Chemical Romance.\r\n<h4>Classic Mustang Style Modernised</h4>\r\nAlder has been used to craft the classic Mustang style body shape which features a handy double cutaway design, providing easy access to the upper frets – perfect for solos and adventurous bass lines.\r\n\r\nSturdy bolt-on construction joins a Maple neck to the Mustang Bass PJ, enhancing mid-range punch.\r\n\r\nThe Mustang Bass also features Fender’s classic short scale length of 30”, making it smaller you’re your usual bass guitars which come in 34” scale.\r\n\r\nThis shorter scale length aids playability, particular for beginner bassists and smaller players but it’s also great for anyone who enjoys that easier reach. Tonal is also enhanced with the Mustang PJ Bass having a tighter top end, more pronounced low end and a scoop in the mid-range.\r\n\r\nThe Pau Ferro fretboard has a 9.5” radius and holds 19 medium jumbo frets along with simple white dot position inlays.\r\n<h4>Vintage Style Electronics</h4>\r\nDelivering fantastically versatile sound, the Fender Mustang Bass comes with a PJ pickup configuration.\r\n\r\nA Vintage Style split single-coil Precision Bass pickup has been installed in the middle pickup position while a Vintage Style single-coil Jazz Bass pickup can be found in the bridge pickup position.\r\n\r\nSelect either of the pickups individually or a combination of the two using the three-way pickup selector switch, while two control knobs in the form of Vintage Style black Jazz Bass knobs allow you to adjust the Master Volume and Master Tone.\r\n<h4>High Quality Hardware</h4>\r\nFour Fender Vintage Style tuning machines with open gear construction can be found at the headstock, providing precise and secure tuning along with some retro visual flair.\r\n\r\nA four-saddle hardtail bridge provides precise intonation and solid tuning stability while increasing sustain.\r\n\r\nFor an extra touch of class, the Mustang Bass has a special neck plate that has been engraved with the classic Fender “F” logo.\r\n<h4>Timeless Style and Versatility</h4>\r\nHugely popular across the globe for more than five decades, the Mustang Bass is one of Fender’s most enduring bass designs.\r\n\r\nAwesome visual presence and excellent Fender craftsmanship along with vintage style pickups in a fantastically versatile PJ configuration makes the Fender Mustang Bass PJ a real all-rounder workhorse bass guitar.\r\n<h4>Fender Mustang Bass PJ in Aged Natural, Key Features:</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Short Scale – 30”</li>\r\n 	<li>Versatile PJ Pickup Configuration</li>\r\n 	<li>Modern “C”-Shaped Neck</li>\r\n 	<li>Vintage Style Tuning Machines</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>Fender Mustang Bass PJ in Aged Natural Specs:</h4>\r\n<h4>Body</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Body Material: Alder</li>\r\n 	<li>Body Finish: Gloss Polyester</li>\r\n 	<li>Body Shape: Mustang Bass</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>Neck</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Neck Material: Maple</li>\r\n 	<li>Neck Finish: Satin Polyurethane</li>\r\n 	<li>Neck Shape: “C” Shape</li>\r\n 	<li>Scale Length: 30” (762mm)</li>\r\n 	<li>Fingerboard Material: Pau Ferro</li>\r\n 	<li>Fingerboard Radius: 9.5” (241mm)</li>\r\n 	<li>Number of Frets: 19</li>\r\n 	<li>Fret Size: Medium Jumbo</li>\r\n 	<li>Nut Material: Synthetic Bone</li>\r\n 	<li>Nut Width: 1.5” (38.1mm)</li>\r\n 	<li>Position Inlays: White Dot</li>\r\n 	<li>Truss Rod: Standard</li>\r\n 	<li>Truss Rod Nut: 3/16” Hex Adjustment</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nElectronics\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Bridge Pickup: Vintage-Style Single-Coil Jazz Bass</li>\r\n 	<li>Middle Pickup: Vintage-Style Split Single-Coil Precision Bass</li>\r\n 	<li>Controls: Master Volume, Master Tone</li>\r\n 	<li>Switching: 3-Position Toggle</li>\r\n 	<li>Configuration: PJ</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>Hardware</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Bridge 4-Saddle Standard</li>\r\n 	<li>Hardware Finish: Nickel/Chrome</li>\r\n 	<li>Tuning Machines: Fender Vintage-Style</li>\r\n 	<li>Pickguard: 4-Ply Tortoiseshell</li>\r\n 	<li>Control Knobs: Vintage Style Black Plastic Jazz Bass</li>\r\n 	<li>Neck Plate: 4-Bolt</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>Miscellaneous</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Strings: Fender USA, NPS, (Gauges .045 - .105)</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Fender Mustang Bass PJ PF', '<strong>Mustang Bass PJ</strong> – another great addition to Fender’s Offset series. Seen here in an retro Aged Natural, this versatile bass gives you the best of both worlds thanks its PJ pickup configuration.', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'fender-mustang-bass-pj-pf', '', '', '2021-09-01 13:56:01', '2021-09-01 12:56:01', '', 0, 'http://localhost/?post_type=product&#038;p=76', 0, 'product', '', 0),
