(79, 1, '2021-08-31 14:53:11', '2021-08-31 13:53:11', 'When it comes to combining vintage aesthetics with modern, high-performance playability, the <strong>Fender American Ultra Precision Bass - </strong>seen here<strong> </strong>in an <strong>Ultraburst </strong>finish - is tough to beat!\r\n<h3>High-Performance, With Versatile Tones</h3>\r\nFeaturing a super-sleek neck, lightweight Alder body, and all-new electronics, the American Ultra Precision is the kind of bass that you could play comfortably for hours at a time, night after night.\r\n<h4>Fender American Ultra Precision Bass RW Ultraburst Highlights</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>A modern, high-performance take on Fender\'s 4-stringed workhorse</li>\r\n 	<li>Lightweight Alder body with a vintage-inspired Ultraburst finish</li>\r\n 	<li>Sleek Maple neck, with a unique \"Modern D\" profile shape, rolled edges, and a tapered neck heel</li>\r\n 	<li>Rosewood fingerboard, with a speedy 10\"-14\" compound-radius fingerboard</li>\r\n 	<li>Ultra Noiseless Split Coil and Single Coil pickup combination</li>\r\n 	<li>Includes deluxe molded hardshell case</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>Crafting The American Ultra P-Bass</h4>\r\nFender\'s American Ultra series has been designed to, quite simply, be the company\'s most advanced lineup of guitars and basses to date.\r\n\r\nWith this P-Bass you get a modern, high-performance take on the quintessential 4-string - a bass designed for the players who demand the very best in terms of tone, versatility, and playability.\r\n\r\nFor starters, there\'s a lightweight Alder body, carved with that familiar dual-cutaway design, and sporting a cool-looking Mocha Burst finish.\r\n\r\nAttached to the body you\'ll find a Maple neck with a unique \"Modern D\" profile, rolled fretboard edges, a tapered neck heel, and a fast-playing compound-radius fingerboard.\r\n\r\nThe end result is a high-performance bass that\'s suitable for any playstyle - the kind you could perform with repeatedly with the minal amount of hand-fatigue, whilst retaining that familiar solid P-Bass feel.\r\n<h4>Ultra Noiseless</h4>\r\nTo deliver the ultimate tonal experience, the American Ultra series features newly-designed Ultra Noiseless pickups - in this case a Split Coil P-bass pickup, and a Single Coil J-Bass bridge position pickup.\r\n\r\nIn addition to the renowned combination of hum-free P-Bass and J-Bass tones, the American Ultra Precision Bass is equipped with cutting-edge wiring options.\r\n\r\nThis wiring offers accurate Cut/Boost options for the Bass, Middle, and Treble frequency ranges, along with a Master Volume, Pan Pot (for pickup selection), and even an Active/Passive mini-toggle, giving you a huge array of tonal options at your disposal.\r\n<h4>Premium-Grade Hardware</h4>\r\nAs a finishing touch, this American Ultra Precision Bass comes equipped with premium-quality hardware to offer levels of stability and reliability that are second-to-none.\r\n\r\nThis includes a set of light-weight, vintage-style tuners, along with a 4-saddle HiMass bridge, which come together to offer incredible levels of tuning stability and pin-point accurate intonation.\r\n<h4>Fender American Ultra Precision Bass RW Mocha Burst Specs</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong>Model Name:</strong> American Ultra Precision Bass, Rosewood Fingerboard, Ultraburst</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Model #:</strong> 0199010712</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Series:</strong> American Ultra</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Country Of Origin:</strong> US</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Color:</strong> Ultraburst</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Body:</strong> Alder</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Body Finish:</strong> Gloss Polyurethane</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Body Shape:</strong> Precision Bass</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Neck Material:</strong> Maple</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Neck Finish:</strong> Satin Urethane with Gloss Urethane Headstock Face</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Neck Shape:</strong> Modern \"D\"</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Scale Length:</strong> 34\" (86.36 cm)</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Fingerboard:</str